@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-5">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-9 mx-auto">
            <h1 class="display-4 mb-4 border-bottom pb-2">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

            <div class="alert alert-info shadow-sm mb-5" role="alert">
                <h4 class="alert-heading">Portfolio Disclosure</h4>
                <p class="mb-0">
                    <strong>IPNoticeHub</strong> is an educational demonstration project created for professional portfolio purposes.
                    This policy outlines how data is handled during your interaction with this technical showcase.
                </p>
            </div>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h2 class="h3"><i class="bi bi-person-badge me-2"></i>1. Information Collection</h2>
                <p>
                    To demonstrate authentication and user-specific data management, we collect minimal personally identifiable information (PII) including:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Account Credentials:</strong> Email address and username provided during registration.</li>
                    <li><strong>Application Data:</strong> Information explicitly entered by the user to generate documents or manage notices.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h2 class="h3"><i class="bi bi-gear-fill me-2"></i>2. Purpose of Processing</h2>
                <p>Your data is processed strictly for the following functional requirements:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>User authentication and session management.</li>
                    <li>Personalization of document templates and system alerts.</li>
                    <li>Demonstrating CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h2 class="h3"><i class="bi bi-cookie me-2"></i>3. Data Security & Storage</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Encryption at Rest:</strong> Industry-standard cryptographic hashing is used to protect user credentials.</li>
                    <li><strong>Controlled Access:</strong> Database connectivity is strictly limited to authorized application components using <strong>identity-based access controls</strong> and private network routing.</li>
                    <li><strong>Zero Trust Architecture:</strong> We follow a "Least Privilege" model to ensure that resources only have the minimum access required to function.</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mb-0">
                    We do not sell, trade, or share your data with external third parties.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-5">
                <h2 class="h3"><i class="bi bi-cookie me-2"></i>4. Third-Party Services & Tracking</h2>
                <p>
                    This application values privacy by design. We do <strong>not</strong> use third-party trackers, advertising networks,
                    or external analytics services (e.g., Google Analytics). Cookies are used solely for essential session persistence.
                </p>
            </section>

            <footer class="mt-5 pt-4 border-top text-muted small">
                <p>Last updated: February 2026</p>
                <p>&copy; 2026 IPNoticeHub &middot; Dedicated to Secure Cloud Engineering</p>
            </footer>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>